// Created on 6 June 2008 by Monica
// This file contains the details about each generator from the
// directory: svn/test/scripts/ 
// each generator displays the path where test files are written

CSL_Auto_Router :: connect() 
      I. Valid tests: 
         - ar_sg_ifc_ifc1.pl => generates valid tests for autorouter using connect method between: 
                                  sg.signal,sg.signal[ps],sg.sg1.signal,sg.sg1.signal[ps], with ifc.ifc1.port;
         - ar_sg_ifc_ifc1_ps.pl => generates valid tests for autorouter using connect method between: 
                                  sg.signal,sg.signal[ps],sg.sg1.signal,sg.sg1.signal[ps], with ifc.ifc1.port[ps];
         - ar_sg_ifc.pl => generates valid tests for autorouter using connect method between: 
                          sg.signal  with ifc.port, and ifc.port with sg.signal;
         - ar_sg_ifc_ps.pl => generates valid tests for autorouter using connect method between: 
                             sg.signal,sg.signal[ps],sg.sg1.signal,sg.sg1.signal[ps], with ifc.port[ps];     
         - ar_sg_op_expr.pl => generates valid tests for autorouter using connect method between: 
                              sg.signal,sg.signal[ps],sg.sg1.signal,sg.sg1.signal[ps], with operation_expression;
         - ar_sg_sig_concat_valid.pl => generates valid tests for autorouter using connect method between: 
                                      sg.signal,sg.signal[ps],sg.sg1.signal,sg.sg1.signal[ps], with concat_expression;
         - ar_sg_sig_replic_valid.pl => generates valid tests for autorouter using connect method between: 
                                      sg.signal,sg.signal[ps],sg.sg1.signal,sg.sg1.signal[ps], with replicate_expression; 
         -ifc_ifc_p_connect_ifc_p.pl => generates valid tests for autorouter using connect method between interfaces;
      

      II.Invalid tests:
         - ar_concat_expr_ifc_invalid.pl => generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between 
                                            a concat_expr and: ifc.port, ifc.port[ps], ifc.ifc1.port,ifc.ifc1.port[ps],
                                                               operation_expression,concat_expression,replicate_expression;
         - ar_op_expr_ifc_invalid.pl => generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between 
                                        a operation_expr and: ifc.port, ifc.port[ps], ifc.ifc1.port,ifc.ifc1.port[ps],
                                                              operation_expression,concat_expression,replicate_expression;
         - ar_port_fifo_invalid.pl => generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between 
                                      a fifo and: port, signal,unit,register_file; 
         - ar_port_rf_invalid.pl => generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between 
                                      a RF and: port,signal,unit,register_file;    
         - ar_port_unit_invalid.pl => generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between 
                                      a unit and: port, signal,fifo,register_file;         
         - ar_sg_sg_invalid.pl => generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between                               
                                  sg.signal,sg.signal[ps],sg.sg1.signal,sg.sg1.signal[ps] with sg.sg1.signal;
         - ar_unit_port_invalid.pl =>generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between 
                                      a unit with port,and RF with port ;  
         - ar_unit_port_ps_invalid.pl =>generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between 
                                      a unit with port[ps],and RF with port[ps];  
         - ar_unit_sig_invalid.pl =>generates invalid tests for autorouter using connect method between 
                                      a unit with signal,and RF with signal ;  
CSL_Language :: Concat & Replicate
      I. Valid tests: 
          - assign_concat.pl =>generates valid tests with concatenation expression on RHS of assign operation.
                                 Assign a concat_expr to a port/signal.Concat_expr contains signals,ports,ports/signals with HIDs 
          - concat_assign_ps.pl =>generates valid tests with concatenation expression on RHS of assign operation.
                                   Assign a concat_expr to a port.Concat_expr contains signals,ports with part_select.
          - concat_expr_valid.pl =>generates valid tests with concat_expr used in RHS and LHS assign operation, used in
                                   f2a,and all legal cases for concat_expr; 
          - ar_replic_in_assign.pl =>generates valid tests with replicate_expr used in RHS assign operation, used in
                                    f2a,and all legal cases for replicate_expr; 
     II.Invalid tests:
          - concat_expr_invalid.pl =>generates invalid tests with concatenation expression used in assign and f2a operation.
                                     The generated tests show the following invalid cases: 
                                     concat_expr on LHS contains the numeric expressions, assign a concat_expr with different
                                     width,operation expression on LHS of assign in concat_expr,use ifc and sg inside of
                                     concat_expr,illegal formal or actual parameter in f2a. 

          - replic_in_assign_invalid.pl =>generates invalid tests with replication expression used in assign  operation.
                                          The generated tests show the following invalid cases: 
                                          replic_expr on LHS, assign a replic_expr with different width,
                                          assign to an operation expression an replic_expr,use ifc and sg inside of
                                          replic_expr or assign to an ifc and a sg a replicate expression. 


CSL_Language :: Csl_Parameter  
      I. Valid tests: 
          - unit_parameter.pl =>generates valid tests for units 
          - reg_parameter.pl=> generates valid tests for register
          - reg_file_fifo_parameter.pl=>generates valid tests for
      register_file and fifo
          - mem_parameter.pl => generates valid tests for memory
          -ifc_sgr_parameter.pl => generates valid tests for
      interfaces and signal_groups
     II.Invalid tests:   
