CSL_Interconnect :: Assign operation
      I. Valid tests: 
         - assign_ifc_ifc.pl => generates valid tests with assign operation between two interfaces,
                                between an interface and an interface with HIDs; 
         - assign.pl => generates valid tests with assign operation
                        between ports, using the operations with ports on RHS; 
         - assign_port_ifc.pl => generates valid tests with assign operation
                                between a port and an interface (with HIDs);
         - assign_port_sg.pl => generates valid tests with assign operation
                                between a port and a signal_group (with HIDs);
         - assign_port_signal.pl => generates valid tests with assign operation
                                   between a port and a signal (with HIDs);
         - assign_replication.pl =>generats valid tests with assign operation between a port/signal
                                   and a replication_expression which contains a port or a signal;
         - assign_sg_sg.pl => generates valid tests with assign operation
                              between a signal_group and a signal_group (with HIDs); 
         - assign_signal_signal.pl => generates valid tests with assign operation
                                      between a signal and a signal (with HIDs); 
 
      II.Invalid tests:

CSL_Interconnect :: Formal to actual
      I. Valid tests: 
          - f2a_port_port.pl => generates valid tests with f2a connection 
                                between two ports and HIDs ports.
      II.Invalid tests:
          -f2a_sg_sg_invalid.pl => generates invalid tests with f2a connection 
                                   using a signal_group/signal as formal.
   